---
import CodexLayout from "../../layouts/CodexLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/cheatsheet-shared.css";
---

<CodexLayout
  title="Codex CLI Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes | changelogs.info"
  description="Get Codex CLI installed and running in 10 minutes. OpenAI's autonomous coding agent."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="cs-wrapper">

    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__emoji">⚡</div>
      <h1 class="cx-headline cs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="cs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-hero__sub">Up and running in 10 minutes — autonomous coding agent that reads your repo, writes code, runs commands.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-grid">

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="cx-headline cs-panel__title">Prerequisites</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Node.js 18+</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Required runtime. Check with <code>node --version</code></p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">OPENAI_API_KEY</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Get your API key from <code>platform.openai.com</code>. Export it in your shell profile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="cx-headline cs-panel__title">Install</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Install globally via npm</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> npm install -g @openai/codex</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="cx-headline cs-panel__title">First Run</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">1. Navigate to your project</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> cd your-project</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">2. Launch Codex</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> codex</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Opens the interactive TUI. Codex reads your repo structure and git history for context.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="cx-headline cs-panel__title">First Real Task</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Add input validation with review</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd cs-item__cmd--accent"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> codex "add input validation to the login form" --approval-mode suggest</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Suggest mode shows you the plan before executing. Perfect for first runs when you want to see what Codex will do.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="cx-headline cs-panel__title">What Next?</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Create instructions file</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Create <code>.codex/instructions.md</code> with build commands and repo conventions. Codex reads it every run.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Try full-auto on a side project</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> codex "refactor utils" --approval-mode auto</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Auto mode lets Codex execute without asking. Great for trusted repos.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/codex-cli/cheatsheet/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Cheatsheet →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">All the commands and workflows at a glance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/codex-cli/tips/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Tips & Tricks →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Quick wins, hidden features, and common mistakes to avoid.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/codex-cli/changelog/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Changelog →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Stay up to date with every release.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</CodexLayout>
